The paper deals with computational complexity and algorithms for problems related to polynomials and ideals, which are central topics in computational algebraic geometry and complexity theory. The use of arithmetic circuits and low rank matrices suggests connections to circuit complexity and linear algebra, which are often studied in cs.CC and cs.SC. The applications to minimum vertex cover and permanent computation suggest connections to graph theory and combinatorics, which are often studied in cs.DS and cs.CG. Finally, the hardness results and parameterized complexity suggest connections to computational complexity and parameterized algorithms, which are often studied in cs.DM.
